snippet.title: What Happens Inside the White House on Inauguration Day
snippet.description:
Ever wonder what happens inside the White House on Inauguration Day? We will examine how the Presidential administration transfers the White House from one President to the next. With a literal army of White House staff, these people have the seemingly impossible task of packing up an entire 20,000-square-foot mansion in a matter of hours two times over. This video will examine the behind-the-scenes action that makes sense of this highly choreographed, organized chaos. Don't miss this behind-the-scenes look at the inauguration of the President of the United States!

snippet.title: Baby Mama Drama or Growth? Ari & Taina Spill ALL While Cooking Chicken Alfredo üç¥üëÄ
snippet.description:
Tonight's episode of Dinner With the Don is EVERYTHING y‚Äôall been waiting for! üëÄ I sat down with Taina (@latainax3), and we had some REAL conversations. We talked about postpartum depression, cleared up whether Taina ever put her hands on Yosohn (y‚Äôall love the tea), and broke down how we‚Äôre navigating baby mama drama to focus on a healthier vibe for the kids. ü´∂ This one‚Äôs all about growth, understanding, and putting the kids first while keeping it authentic.

üíÑ Ari‚Äôs Look Brought to You By Remedy By Ari

Buttercake Cream Gloss: https://remedybyari.com/collections/lip-gloss/products/buttercake-cream-gloss
Baby Girl Lip Liner: https://remedybyari.com/collections/lip-liners/products/baby-girl-liner


And of course, we had to chef it up in the kitchen too! üç¥ We made a creamy, delicious Chicken Alfredo that‚Äôs perfect for dinner tonight while you tune in. Scroll down for the ingredients and step-by-step instructions to cook along with us. Trust me, this recipe is a vibe. üëá



Ingredients:
Heavy whipping cream (1 quart)
Mozzarella cheese (shredded)
Italian cheese (shredded)
Parmesan cheese (shredded)
Fresh basil
Alfredo sauce
Garlic paste
Chicken cutlets
Lemon
Vinegar
Fettuccine noodles
Garlic powder
Onion powder
Black pepper
Chicken bouillon
Adobo
Saz√≥n
Old Bay
Tony‚Äôs seasoning
Eggs
Flour
Bread crumbs
Canola oil
Cooking Instructions:
Boil the Fettuccine Noodles

Bring a pot of salted water to a boil. Add your fettuccine noodles and cook for about 10 minutes or until al dente. Strain and set aside.
Clean & Season the Chicken

Put on gloves and wash the chicken cutlets with lemon and vinegar, making sure to remove all the slime.
Season the chicken generously with chicken bouillon, garlic powder, onion powder, black pepper, adobo, saz√≥n, and Old Bay (Taina‚Äôs fave üíÅ‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è). Let the chicken marinate while you prep the sauce.
Start the Sauce

In a medium skillet, pour in half a quart of heavy whipping cream to start. Add a handful each of mozzarella, Italian, and Parmesan cheeses, and whisk slowly over low heat.
Add garlic paste and season with black pepper, onion powder, garlic powder, Tony‚Äôs seasoning, fresh basil, and a little Alfredo sauce. Keep whisking as it thickens, and slowly add more heavy whipping cream to get the perfect creamy consistency.
Bread & Fry the Chicken

Set up your breading station with bread crumbs, flour, and beaten eggs. Coat each chicken cutlet in bread crumbs first, then flour, and finally dip it into the egg wash.
Heat canola oil in a skillet and fry the chicken until golden brown and fully cooked through.
Bring It All Together

Toss the fettuccine noodles into the sauce, making sure they‚Äôre coated in all that creamy goodness.
Serve the noodles on a plate with the fried chicken cutlets on top. Garnish with fresh basil and a little extra Parmesan cheese if you‚Äôre feeling fancy.

Don‚Äôt miss this juicy, heartfelt episode. Laughs, growth, and a bomb Chicken Alfredo recipe‚Äîwhat more could you ask for? And don‚Äôt forget to tag me if you recreate this dish! üòç

#DinnerWithTheDon #Therealkylesister #LatainaX3 #BabyMamaChronicles #ChickenAlfredoRecipe

snippet.title: How the LA wildfires unfolded and what‚Äôs needed for recovery | BBC News
snippet.description:
As Los Angeles faces its most destructive wildfires in history, tens of thousands of buildings have been destroyed, and hundreds of thousands have been forced to flee their homes. 

The largest blaze, in the Pacific Palisades area, has burned more than 23,000 acres, making it the city‚Äôs worst fire on record.

To grasp the scale, the affected area stretches across large parts of lower Manhattan and Queens in New York.

In this BBC News special, we hear from those on the front line and the people who have lost their homes and livelihoods to the disaster.

Subscribe here: http://bit.ly/1rbfUog

For more news, analysis and features visit: www.bbc.com/news

snippet.title: Structures Burn as Palisades Fire Explodes to 1,200+ Acres
snippet.description:
PACIFIC PALISADES, CA (CNS) ‚Äì A brush fire driven by fierce Santa Ana winds scorched over 1,200 acres in Pacific Palisades Tuesday, damaging homes, forcing thousands to evacuate, and threatening over 13,200 structures. No injuries were reported.

The fire, reported around 10:30 a.m. near Piedra Morada and Monte Hermoso drives, quickly grew to 1,262 acres by mid-afternoon with no containment. Mandatory evacuations covered much of Pacific Palisades, displacing 30,000 residents. Evacuation routes clogged as vehicles were abandoned, and some residents fled on foot.

Evacuation centers opened at Westwood Recreation Center for people and Pierce College for large animals, while smaller animals were directed to the Agoura Animal Care Center. Air tankers and water-dropping helicopters joined firefighters battling the flames, but strong winds hindered containment.

Malibu issued evacuation warnings for areas between Carbon Beach Terrace and Las Flores Mesa Drive. By evening, the fire spread south to the coastline and west toward Malibu, jumping Tuna Canyon Road. Multiple structures, including homes and possibly parts of Palisades Charter High School, were destroyed.

The Getty Villa remained safe thanks to fire mitigation efforts, though vegetation on the site burned. Museum galleries were sealed off from smoke with state-of-the-art systems, and water storage and irrigation were deployed to protect the property.

Road closures included portions of the Pacific Coast Highway, the 10 Freeway, and Sunset Boulevard, complicating evacuation efforts.

Amid red flag warnings, officials anticipated worsening conditions overnight as winds intensified. Emergency declarations were issued by local and state authorities, with Governor Gavin Newsom securing federal assistance. President Joe Biden approved a Fire Management Assistance Grant to support firefighting costs.

City officials relocated students from several schools, including Palisades Charter Elementary and Paul Revere Middle School, to safer locations. The South Coast AQMD issued a smoke advisory, warning of unhealthy air quality and advising residents to stay indoors.

LAFD Chief Kristin Crowley and Mayor Karen Bass urged residents to comply with evacuation orders. ‚ÄúThis is a very dangerous situation,‚Äù Bass said.

The fire's cause remains under investigation.
